data.text:
Group➨001➨Subgroup➨02➨Subgroup➨01-Y9389➨Family➨Samuel Jackson & Margaret Cree

The first known documented instance of Samuel Jackson was his participation with the Pennsylvania militia during the Sandusky Expedition in 1782. Family legend has it that he came over to the United States as a British soldier and then somehow ended up serving with the Colonials.
